cast_shell: install FakeConnectivityChecker, drop gstatic.com probe

ConnectivityCheckerImpl probes
https://connectivitycheck.gstatic.com/generate_204 every few seconds.
On this device there is no upstream DNS / direct egress and the
checker storms the log with

    Connectivity check failed: net_error=-105
    Notify connectivity check failure.

forever. Nothing in the kiosk path observes Connected() state - the
checker is purely Cast plumbing for an offline / soft-online overlay
the webapp does not render. FakeConnectivityChecker is already in the
connectivity_checker source set unconditionally (the IS_FUCHSIA guard
in this file is only because Fuchsia was the prior in-tree user); it
reports always-connected with zero network traffic and zero log spam.

This patch drops the platform guard around the fake header include
and swaps the real checker for the fake at construction time.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [kiosk-specific use case]

Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>

--- a/chromecast/browser/cast_browser_main_parts.cc
+++ b/chromecast/browser/cast_browser_main_parts.cc
